<DATE>2 April 2001</DATE>
</REFSECT1INFO>
<TITLE>Description
</TITLE>
<PARA>
<FUNCTION>verrx</FUNCTION> displays a formatted error message on the 
standard error output. The last component of the program name, a 
<TOKEN>COLON</TOKEN> character, and a <TOKEN>SPACE</TOKEN> are output. 
If <PARAMETER>fmt</PARAMETER> is not <TOKEN>NULL</TOKEN>, the formatted 
error message, a <TOKEN>COLON</TOKEN>, and a <TOKEN>SPACE</TOKEN> are 
output. The output is followed by a <TOKEN>newline</TOKEN> character.
</PARA>
<PARA>
<FUNCTION>verrx</FUNCTION> does not return, but exits with the value 
of <PARAMETER>eval</PARAMETER>.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>
